Feedback — rubric-based


I grade assignments using this rubric: Content (40%), Structure (30%), Referencing (20%), Language (10%).

Here is how I wrote feedback for two students:

STUDENT A (Score: 78/100):
Content (32/40): Strong understanding of core concepts, minor gaps in application.
Structure (24/30): Logical flow, but introduction is too brief.
Referencing (16/20): Good use of sources; two citations missing page numbers.
Language (6/10): Mostly clear; some run-on sentences.
Overall: A well-researched paper. Improve your introduction and citation formatting.

STUDENT B (Score: 55/100):
Content (20/40): Key concepts mentioned but not adequately explained.
Structure (16/30): Sections are disjointed; lacks clear transitions.
Referencing (12/20): Only 4 sources used; minimum is 8.
Language (7/10): Writing is clear and grammatically correct.
Overall: Revisit the core concepts and expand your research base before resubmission.

